  "An economist models a 3-sector economy with input-output matrix A = [[0.1, 0.2, 0.1], [0.2, 0.1, 0.3], [0.1, 0.3, 0.1]]. The column sums are 0.4, 0.6, and 0.5. Is the Hawkins-Simon condition likely satisfied?": "",
